The paper discusses the use of network steganography in malware and other malicious activities, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the technical aspects of network steganography, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper mentions the potential use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to detect network steganography. The paper also discusses the challenges of countering network steganography in practice, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
